Attention!  AKC does not register the Black or Red Airedales.  They will be registered with WorldATR.  Black and tan puppies born from a black or red parent will not be registered AKC, but will be registered with WorldATR.  If this is important to you, make sure you let us know so we can reserve you a puppy from an AKC litter.  ALL our Airedales are purebred, regardless of color! 

We register with two registries:  
WorldATR ~ World Airedale Terrier Registry 
AKC ~ American Kennel Club


Limited vs. Unlimited Registrations:
Limited Registration means your dog is registered, but offspring cannot be registered.
Unlimited Registration means your dog is registered, and any offspring may also be registered as long as the other adult dog is registered as well.

Every breeder has the right and responsibility to determine to whom will have breeding rights (unlimited registration).  Puppy buyers interested in purchasing unlimited breeding rights should visit with the breeder before purchasing.  This gives the breeder the ability to protect the integrity and characteristics of the Airedale breed and specific pedigree bloodlines.

All breeders big, small, one time or ten times have the responsibilities of caring for the integrity and traits of the Airedale breed.  The original purpose for which the breed was developed is in the hands of those who continue to produce offspring.

Should you purchase the unlimited breeding rights, please be understanding, respectful and careful to preserve the breed traits we all love so much in the Airedale Terrier breed.


What this means to you:
You will receive a WorldATR registration form in the mail.  The form will be marked Limited Registration unless other arrangements have been made between you and the breeder.  You fill out your section of the form and mail along with a check to the address on the form.

In the case that both sire and dam are AKC registered, the pups may be registered with AKC as well.

