How & Why we are involved with WorldATR:
We started breeding Airedales around 2001.  We wanted to keep a small kennel of pets and hunting dogs in the standard black & tan, black, and red airedales.  As people continued to call wanting all three colors, we bred our dogs to continue their great bloodlines and characteristics.  We have met some amazing people across the country, who are using the pups we produced for many purposes.

As we expanded and became better aquainted with other Airedale breeders, we noticed a common complaint with certain registries.  Soon several breeders were talking to us about starting an exclusive registry for the Airedale Terriers.  We were reluctant to do this because of the lifetime commitment it would require and the credibility it may take from both the registry and our kennel.  

One registry we were using became unreliable.  It took up to six months to get registration papers back.  Other breeders complained that they had clients who had been waiting 18 months for papers and were not sure they would ever get them.   After pondering and being encouraged by other breeders for about a year, we decided to start World Airedale Terrier Registry.  We have committed to operate this registry with utmost integrity.  These are two separate entities and will be run as such.
